content: Kelsey Chalmers submitted her PhD in 2019 at the University of Sydney, and investigated the measurement of low-value procedures in Australian private health insurance claims. Prior to this, she studied and worked at the University of Queensland where she received a University Medal for her Bachelor of Science. During her PhD she was a scholarship recipient at the Capital Markets Cooperative Research Centre (in the Health Market Quality program) and a visiting Queen Elizabeth scholar at McMaster University.
